\p 
\v 24 The Lord told Moses,
\v 25 “Tell Aaron and his sons that these are the regulations for the sin offering. The sin offering is to be killed where the burnt offering is killed before the Lord, and it is most holy.
\v 26 The priest who offers the sin offering is to eat it. It must be eaten without yeast in \w a|strong="H3068"\w* holy place—the courtyard of the Tent of Meeting.
\v 27 Whatever touches it shall become holy and if any of the blood is splashed on clothing, you must wash it in \w a|strong="H3068"\w* holy place.
\v 28 The clay pot used to boil the sin offering must be broken. If it's boiled in \w a|strong="H3068"\w* bronze pot, the pot must be thoroughly cleaned and washed out with water.
\v 29 Any male among the priests may eat it, it is most holy.
\v 30 But no sin offering may be eaten if its blood has been taken into the Tent of Meeting as \w a|strong="H3068"\w* means to make things right in the Holy Place. In that case it must be burned.”
\b
\c 7
\p 
